  ## Minor Crimes
  - Warnings should be issued for a first offense.
  - If multiple minor crimes have been committed or it is a repeat offense, then 5 minutes is the maximum sentence for a minor crime.
  <Table Columns="4">
    <ColorBox>
      <Box>
        Offense
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box>
        Description
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box>
        Notes
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box>
        Code
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#2e422e">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Petty Theft (H)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To take non-vital or inexpensive property of another individual, organization, or common property, without
        consent.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Petty theft covers the owning or possession of items that were not lawfully or consentually given to the holder.
        This may include departmental contraband if the contraband was not approved for the holder.
        Items covered by petty theft are usually easily replaceable, low-value, or low-danger.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        1-01
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#453a59">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Vandalism (D)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To intentionally deface or superficially damage public or private property.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Painting obscene graffiti, smashing bar glasses, breaking lights, and eating a crewmember's plushie is vandalism, breaking a window into
        space or secure areas is not.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        1-02
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#59563a">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Trespass (T)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To enter a non-secured area without permission.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        It's best to just remove them from the area unless this is a repeated crime.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        1-03
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#4d2e2e">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Animal Cruelty (V)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To inflict unnecessary suffering or harm on a non-sapient being with malicious intent.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        This doesn’t include legitimate and authorized animal testing and usually doesn't extend to vermin such as mice, animals normally used in the process of food production, or creatures
        that could pose a threat to the station.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        1-04
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#4d2e2e">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Endangerment (V)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To recklessly put yourself or others in danger, either through direct action or failure to act.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Covers industrial accidents, industrial negligence, self-experimentation, or even medical malpractice.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        1-05
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#3b4354">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Disturbance (R)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To cause a public disturbance.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Sometimes referred to as hooliganism. The catch-all for obnoxious crewmates. Covers things such as public
        nudity, needless insults, obstructing authorities, and inciting crime or violence.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        1-06
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
  </Table>

  ## Moderate Crimes
  - The maximum sentence for a moderate crime is 5 minutes.
  - Depending on the situation, you may want to issue a warning instead of detaining.
  <Table Columns="4">
    <ColorBox>
      <Box>
        Offense
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box>
        Description
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box>
        Notes
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box>
        Code
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
  <ColorBox Color="#593a4e">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Resisting a Lawful Search (E)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To resist a reasonable or lawful search or seizure by a member of the security department, or an authorized head of staff.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        The search or seizure must be legal, either through a valid warrant, evidence, or alert level.
        The perpetrator must have made an active attempt to flee, resist restraint, or refuse to hand over contraband if applicable.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        2-00
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#2e422e">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Grand Theft (H)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To take critical or unreplaceable property of another individual or organization without consent.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        The difference between theft and grand theft is based on how crucial the stolen item is, this mostly is
        used for the theft of command staff items, things like door remotes, hardsuits, jetpacks, and unreplaceable
        machine parts. Additionally, stealing anything from the armory is grand theft, including seized contraband.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        2-01
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#453a59">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Damage of Property (D)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To maliciously damage or deface public or private property or equipment.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Includes destruction of job equipment, such as hydro trays, booze dispensers, and chemical dispensers. Step up from
        vandalism but a step down from critical property destruction.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        2-02
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#59563a">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Secure Trespass (T)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To enter a secured area without permission.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        This covers places like telecomms, head offices, security zones, command areas, the vault, and the armory.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        2-03
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#4d2e2e">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Assault (V)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To threaten to or to use physical force against a member of the crew without the intent to kill.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Attempted murder and assault are different; a fist fight is most likely assault. A shooting may be an
        attempted murder. Ensure you have context before making the call.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        2-04
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#4d2e2e">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Gross Negligence (V)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        A conscious, reckless disregard for the safety or  of others.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To cause an unreasonable amount of damage to a part of the station as a result of negligence. This
        could be purposefully allowing anomalies to go critical, or causing an accidental but not permanent
        death.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        2-05
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
  </Table>

  ## Major Crimes
  - The maximum sentence for a major crime is 10 minutes.
  - It is recommended not to use maximum sentences for those being compliant.
  <Table Columns="4">
    <ColorBox>
      <Box>
        Offense
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
