      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Breach of Custody (E)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To break out of a cell or custody with the intention of escaping.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Includes breaking out other people.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        4-00
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#453a59">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Major Sabotage/Destruction (D)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To cause massive damage to an area or major station system.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        This is mostly used for deadly departmental bombings or sabotage of major station systems
        such as the TEG or hacking the ATS.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        4-02
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#4d2e2e">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Attempted Murder (V)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To try to use force against a crewmember with the clear intent to kill.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        This covers any intentional but unsuccessful attempt to kill another member of the crew.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        4-04
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox Color="#4d2e2e">
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Manslaughter (V)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To incidentally kill a crewmember being without intent.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Includes manslaughter in self-defense and negligent manslaughter.
        If there is provable intent, then the subject should instead be charged with attempted murder.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        4-05
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
  </Table>

  ## Capital Crimes
  - Capital crimes should usually lead to a death sentence or shift lasting detainment.
  <Table Columns="4">
    <ColorBox>
      <Box>
        Offense
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
